.ne 2
.mk
.na
.B PATH
.ad
.RS 24n
.rt
Sets the initial shell
.B PATH
variable.
.RE

.sp
.ne 2
.mk
.na
.B SUPATH
.ad
.RS 24n
.rt
Sets the initial shell
.B PATH
variable for root.
.RE

.sp
.ne 2
.mk
.na
.B TIMEOUT
.ad
.RS 24n
.rt
Sets the number of seconds (between
.B 0
and
.BR 900 )
to wait before
abandoning a login session.
.RE

.sp
.ne 2
.mk
.na
.B UMASK
.ad
.RS 24n
.rt
Sets the initial shell file creation mode mask. See
.BR umask (1).
.RE

.sp
.ne 2
.mk
.na
.B SYSLOG
.ad
.RS 24n
.rt
Determines whether the \fBsyslog\fR(3C) \fBLOG_AUTH\fR facility should be
used to log all root logins at level
.B LOG_NOTICE
and multiple failed
login attempts at\fBLOG_CRIT\fR.
.RE

.sp
.ne 2
.mk
.na
.B DISABLETIME
.ad
.RS 24n
.rt
If present, and greater than zero, the number of seconds that \fBlogin\fR
waits after
.B RETRIES
failed attempts or the
.B PAM
framework returns
.BR PAM_ABORT .
Default is
.B 20
seconds. Minimum is
.B 0
seconds. No
maximum is imposed.
.RE

.sp
.ne 2
.mk
.na
.B SLEEPTIME
.ad
.RS 24n
.rt
If present, sets the number of seconds to wait before the login failure
message is printed to the screen. This is for any login failure other than
.BR PAM_ABORT .
Another login attempt is allowed, providing
.B RETRIES
has
not been reached or the
.B PAM
framework is returned
.BR PAM_MAXTRIES .
Default is
.B 4
seconds. Minimum is
.B 0
.RB "seconds. Maximum is" " 5"
seconds.
.sp
Both \fBsu\fR(1M) and \fBsulogin\fR(1M) are affected by the value of
.BR SLEEPTIME .
.RE

.sp
.ne 2
.mk
.na
.B RETRIES
.ad
.RS 24n
.rt
Sets the number of retries for logging in (see \fBpam\fR(3PAM)). The default
is 5. The maximum number of retries is 15. For accounts configured with
automatic locking (see
.B SECURITY
above), the account is locked and
.B login
exits. If automatic locking has not been configured, \fBlogin\fR
exits without locking the account.
.RE

.sp
.ne 2
.mk
.na
.B SYSLOG_FAILED_LOGINS
.ad
.RS 24n
.rt
Used to determine how many failed login attempts are allowed by the system
before a failed login message is logged, using the
.BR syslog (3C)
.B LOG_NOTICE
facility. For example, if the variable is set to
.BR 0 ,
.B login
logs
.I all
failed login attempts.
.RE

